                <head>The Message and the Reports</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"The Message...furnish[es] no grounds upon which to found a hope that the
                    blessings of peace will soon smile upon our unhappy country or that the blood or
                    the money of the people is at all to be economized."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Item unhappily and critically reports that Lincoln's message did not lead
                    to any hope that peace will soon be restored. Article expresses consternation
                    regarding the increase in taxation that will be passed to finance the war
                    effort.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Reports of Army movements. News from Fortress Monroe in column 6.</pageNote>
